RT @NYDailyNews: A giant cloud of Saharan dust is expected to reach the U.S. after traveling more than 5,000 miles from Africa and blanketing many Caribbean islands.

A picture taken from the ISS shows the band of dust covering hundreds of miles over the Atlantic Ocean.
